ies and challenges presented by the current agenda. It will be widely welcomed by tutors and practitioners alike, enabling readers to make sense of the legislation and national guidance, and to understand better the new agendas for children's services. For more information visit: http://www.everychildmattersbook.co.uk/  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aChild welfarezGreat Britain. 0aEducationxStandardszGreat Britain. 0aFamily serviceszGreat Britain. 0aInteragency coordinationzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Children's Studies.2bisacsh1 aBarker, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarker, Richard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBarker, Sue, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBroadhead, Pat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrownrigg, Allan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampbell, Steve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCookson, Lindey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGodfrey, Lesli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraham, Pamela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHunter, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHutchinson, Fiona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMachin, Alison I., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, Douglas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSanter, Joan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196